name: Silverspur Pouch
description:
Soft leather pouch with a vintage embroidered doily. Finished with a dainty scene of spring birds etched in a glass button. One-of-a-kind O/S


Just a side note: This piece is part of the "Tigerlilly" look from the 2011 Autumn/Winter Collection "Somewhere in Old Wyoming". This collection was inspired by (and pays a homage to) many childhood trips to Cody, Wyoming with my family. It incorporates 1950's cuts with a cheeky spin on the classic dichotomy of Cowboys and Indians of the West. Each garment is slightly idiosyncratic and witty; all are punctuated with personalized details like embroidered monograms, hand stitched lines from meaningful poetry, and countless subtle (and sometimes hidden) details.

name: Nautical Knot Croptop
description:
Textured white crop (main fabric, circa 1970's), adorned with hand-tied knots. Pearl inlayed snaps. One-of-a-kind Size: S


Just a side not: This item is part of the "Wooden Pearls" collection...here's a little Cait the Great commentary on the idea:

"It all started during an epic drive to the ocean a about a month ago. I fell in love with the colors and textures and thought they were a perfect thing to work with during these sunny months. It's a pretty simple (and I'll be honest--overused) concept, but think my take will give you more of a "the-mermaid-from-Splash-meets-Tom-Hanks-in-Castaway" feel, Like magical driftwood or something." -Cait the Great, Summer 2011

name: Haiku Frock
description:
Hand-dyed in black & green teas, this oversized tank (arguably a frock) is gently aged with whimsical charm. A hand embroidered tri-scene pays homage through imagery to an original haiku by Ryusui. The haiku reads "in all this cool, is the moon also sleeping, there in the pool?". Cotton doilies and intricate hand-embroidered finishing punctuate this piece. Note: every alteration and finishing is done entirely by hand and the garment should be handled with care. Hand wash and hang dry please! Size: O/S 
One-of-a-kind
